I used Google Forms to create a Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz for my batchmates. The form included exactly five questions covering basic concepts such as digital literacy, online safety, strong passwords, and useful digital tools for students. I ensured that the quiz had a mix of question types, including multiple-choice and short answer questions, to make it interactive and easy to attempt.
While creating the form, I also explored features like adding answer validation and viewing responses through the linked Google Sheet. This helped me understand how data can be collected and analyzed efficiently. Designing the questions in a clear and simple way was important so that all students could easily understand and respond.
This activity helped me learn how online tools like Google Forms can be used for academic purposes such as quizzes, surveys, and feedback collection. In the future, I can use this tool to conduct class surveys, collect project feedback, or even create practice quizzes for exams. Overall, it was a useful and practical experience that improved my digital and collaboration skills.
